---
title: Italian Wedding Soup with Mini Meatballs, Couscous & Kale
description: The name “wedding soup” supposedly comes from the perfect marriage of all its ingredients, but we like to think it’s because the soup is so good, you could make it your one and only. This version stars bite-size mini meatballs that float in an herby, aromatic broth with chewy couscous, tender kale, sweet onion and carrot, and rich Parmesan. It’s pretty easy to see why all of this is a match made in heaven.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/italian-wedding-soup-b406ebbb.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/italian-wedding-soup-5fc6c5f99072d15ffa65c4f6-19627063.pdf
servings: 2
cuisine: Italian
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
time required: 45 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 33 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 43 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1330 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/italian-wedding-soup-5fc6c5f99072d15ffa65c4f6
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}; mince some onion until you have 2 TBSP
(4 TBSP for 4 servings). Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Trim, peel, and
thinly slice @carrot{3%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick rounds.

In a large #bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup},
minced onion, half the garlic, half the @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}
(you'll use the rest later), @salt{3/4%tsp} (1¼ tsp for 4 servings), and
@pepper{}. Form into 14-16 1-inch meatballs (28-32 meatballs for 4).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a medium #pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add meatballs and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over,
~{3-6%minutes} (they'll finish cooking in step 5). Tip: Be sure not to crowd the
pot. Cook in batches if necessary. Turn off heat; transfer meatballs to a #plate{}.
Carefully wash out pot.

Return same pot to medium-high heat. Add a drizzle of olive oil, diced onion,
and carrot; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly softened,
~{3-4%minutes}. Add remaining garlic and Italian seasoning; cook until fragrant,
~{30%seconds}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @water{3 1/2%cups}
(6 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a simmer.

Meanwhile, remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop or cut any
large pieces if necessary. Add half the kale and half the @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}
(all the kale and couscous for 4 servings) to pot. Cook until couscous and carrot
are tender and kale has softened, ~{8-10%minutes}. In the last ~{2-3%minutes} of
cooking, return meatballs to pot and cook until cooked through. Taste and season
generously with salt and pepper.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Top with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and serve.